(
  'Puget Sound Navy Museum',
  'A free naval history museum in downtown Bremerton with two floors of exhibits, a Family Discovery Room for kids, and interactive displays about life in the U.S. Navy past and present. Right next to the ferry terminal — combine it with the boat ride for a great day trip.',
  '251 1st St, Bremerton, WA 98337',
  'https://maps.google.com/?q=Puget+Sound+Navy+Museum+Bremerton',
  47.5627, -122.6246,
  'activity',
  '{"All Ages", "3-5", "5+", "8+"}',
  'Wider PNW',
  'Free',
  '{"Rainy Day", "Chill / Easy", "Special / Treat"}',
  'The ferry ride from Seattle to Bremerton is half the fun — kids love it and it''s included in the fare. The museum itself is free, genuinely kid-friendly, and has a dedicated Family Discovery Room with hands-on activities. Combine it with a walk through the USS Turner Joy (a decommissioned destroyer docked right next door) and you''ve got a full day adventure that costs almost nothing. Great rainy day option since most of it is indoors.',
  '{"No dedicated parking — use the free lots on 5th Street and walk down Pacific Ave", "The museum is fairly small — plan for 1-2 hours max, not a full day on its own", "Closed Tuesdays", "The ferry from Seattle takes about an hour each way — factor that into your schedule", "USS Turner Joy is a separate admission and has steep ladders — not great for toddlers or strollers"}',
  'Take the Seattle-Bremerton ferry from Colman Dock — it''s a beautiful ride and way more fun than driving. Walk on as foot passengers to skip parking hassles on both ends. The museum is a 5-minute walk from the Bremerton ferry terminal.',
  '[{"name": "El Balcon", "description": "Solid Mexican food within walking distance of the museum"}, {"name": "The Curry", "description": "Indian restaurant a short walk away in downtown Bremerton"}, {"name": "Fraiche Cup", "description": "Coffee and quick bites near the waterfront"}, {"name": "Pack snacks for the ferry", "description": "The ferry has a cafeteria but packing is cheaper and easier with kids"}]',
  null, null, null,
